import sys

S = sys.stdin.readline().strip()

char_count = {}
for char in S:
    if char in char_count:
        char_count[char] += 1
    else:
        char_count[char] = 1

two_count = sum(1 for count in char_count.values() if count == 2)

if two_count == 2:
    print("Yes")
else:
    print("No")

This Python code reads the input string S, counts the occurrences of each character in the string, and checks if there are exactly two characters that occur twice. If so, it prints "Yes"; otherwise, it prints "No".
